<https://w3id.org/hse/ontology/phi#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/abstract> "The Population Health Indicator Ontology (phi) provides a formal vocabulary for describing population health indicators, their definitions, data sources, methodologies, and quality attributes. Developed as part of the Older Adult Health and Wellbeing Profile project. Funded by Health Service Executive National Clinical Programme for Older People Research Award 2024 (NCPOP RA3/2024)" .
<https://w3id.org/hse/ontology/phi#> <http://purl.org/dc/terms/bibliographicCitation> "Rob Brennan, Junli Liang and Akila Wickramasekara, Prototyping a Health DCAT-AP data catalogue to support population health indicator identification and quality assessment, NeXt-generation Data Governance workshop 2025 (NXDG 2025), https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-4064/NXDG25-paper3.pdf; Mohamed Chouaiech, Pascal Derycke, Bert Van Nuffelen, Nuno Miguel Soares Mesquita, Pavlina Fragkou, Charles-Andrew Vande Catsyne, Truls Korsgaard, Hans Aage Huru, and Makx Dekkers, HealthDCAT-AP Release 5 22 September 2025, Available at https://healthdataeu.pages.code.europa.eu/healthdcat-ap/releases/release-5/" .
